The paper deals with the practical implementation of Polar decoders, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The proposed architecture involves hardware optimization, which falls under the category of computer architecture and embedded systems (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the use of look-up tables and indexing, which are techniques commonly used in electronic engineering and signal processing (cs.ET). The paper presents a new approach to parallelizing the decoding process, which involves generating multiple candidate paths simultaneously, a topic related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with error patterns and syndromes, which are concepts commonly used in coding theory and error correction (cs.SY).
